---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Nav from '../components/Nav.astro';
import SiteFooter from '../components/SiteFooter.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Our Work | ProActive Pixels — AI & Automation Case Studies"
  description="Real results from real businesses. See how ProActive Pixels finds automation leaks and fixes them — with specific timelines, solutions, and outcomes."
>
  <Nav currentPage="work" />

  <main>

    <!-- PAGE HERO -->
    <section class="page-hero">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="section-label fade-in">Case Studies</div>
        <h1 class="page-headline fade-in fade-in-delay-1">
          Real Leaks.<br>
          <span class="headline-accent">Real Results.</span>
        </h1>
        <p class="page-sub fade-in fade-in-delay-2">
          Every engagement starts with a free audit. Here's what we've found — and what happened after we fixed it.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- RESULTS BAR -->
    <div class="results-bar fade-in">
      <div class="container results-bar-inner">
        <div class="results-stat results-stat--hero">
          <span class="stat-num">100%</span>
          <span class="stat-label">of solutions still running</span>
        </div>
        <div class="results-divider" aria-hidden="true"></div>
        <div class="results-pair">
          <div class="results-pair-stat">
            <span class="stat-num stat-num--md">72 hrs</span>
            <span class="stat-label">avg. time to live</span>
          </div>
          <div class="results-pair-sep" aria-hidden="true"></div>
          <div class="results-pair-stat">
            <span class="stat-num stat-num--md">30 days</span>
            <span class="stat-label">avg. time to ROI</span>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="results-divider" aria-hidden="true"></div>
        <div class="results-note">
          <p>The audit is <strong>always free.</strong><br>No commitment, no pitch.</p>
          <a href="/assessment" class="results-note-link">Start yours →</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- CASE STUDIES -->
    <section class="section-cases">
      <div class="container">

        <!-- Case Study 1 -->
        <article class="case-study fade-in">
          <div class="case-meta">
            <span class="case-industry">HVAC</span>
            <span class="case-type">Voice AI Receptionist</span>
          </div>
          <div class="case-inner">
            <div class="case-text">
              <h2 class="case-title">HVAC Company Recovering $18K in the First Month</h2>
              <div class="case-section">
                <h3 class="case-section-label">The Leak</h3>
                <p>A regional HVAC company had strong word-of-mouth and steady ad spend — but 43% of their inbound calls happened after hours or during job sites when no one could answer. Those calls went to voicemail. Most didn't call back. The owner estimated he was losing 3–5 jobs per week to missed calls, but had no way to confirm until we audited.</p>
              </div>
              <div class="case-section">
                <h3 class="case-section-label">What We Implemented</h3>
                <p>A Voice AI receptionist configured with their exact service area, job types, and qualification questions. It answers every call — day or night — qualifies the lead, books appointments directly into their scheduling system, and sends a follow-up text confirming the booking.</p>
              </div>
              <div class="case-section">
                <h3 class="case-section-label">The Result</h3>
                <p>Live in 68 hours. Three booked jobs in week one — all from calls that previously went to voicemail. In month one, the owner attributed $18K in new revenue directly to calls the AI answered that he would have missed. The system is still running with zero issues at month six.</p>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="case-stats">
              <div class="case-stat case-stat--primary">
                <span class="case-stat-num">$18K</span>
                <span class="case-stat-label">Revenue recovered in month 1</span>
              </div>
              <div class="case-stat">
                <span class="case-stat-num">68hrs</span>
                <span class="case-stat-label">From kickoff to live</span>
              </div>
              <div class="case-stat">
                <span class="case-stat-num">100%</span>
                <span class="case-stat-label">Call answer rate (was 57%)</span>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </article>

        <!-- Case Study 2 -->
        <article class="case-study fade-in">
          <div class="case-meta">
            <span class="case-industry">Med Spa</span>
            <span class="case-type">Intake & Scheduling Automation</span>
          </div>
          <div class="case-inner">
            <div class="case-text">
              <h2 class="case-title">Med Spa Reclaims 14 Hours Per Week From Manual Admin</h2>
              <div class="case-section">
                <h3 class="case-section-label">The Leak</h3>
                <p>A busy med spa's front desk team was spending 2+ hours per day on intake forms, appointment confirmations, and follow-up calls for no-shows. The same questions asked manually, over and over. Staff were burned out and booking capacity was being left on the table because the team was too buried in admin to handle new leads promptly.</p>
              </div>
              <div class="case-section">
                <h3 class="case-section-label">What We Implemented</h3>
                <p>An automated intake flow that sends new clients a form link immediately after booking, populates their information directly into the practice management system, and sends automated reminders at 48 hours and 2 hours before appointments. No-shows get an automatic re-book sequence. Confirmation calls were eliminated.</p>
              </div>
              <div class="case-section">
                <h3 class="case-section-label">The Result</h3>
                <p>14 hours of staff time saved per week. The front desk team was redeployed to client experience — following up with post-treatment clients and handling upsells — which added measurable revenue on top of the cost savings. The owner estimated total value at $4,200/month between time saved and additional bookings captured.</p>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="case-stats">
              <div class="case-stat case-stat--primary">
                <span class="case-stat-num">14hrs</span>
                <span class="case-stat-label">Staff time saved per week</span>
              </div>
              <div class="case-stat">
                <span class="case-stat-num">$4.2K</span>
                <span class="case-stat-label">Estimated monthly value</span>
              </div>
              <div class="case-stat">
                <span class="case-stat-num">72hrs</span>
                <span class="case-stat-label">From kickoff to live</span>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </article>

        <!-- Case Study 3 -->
        <article class="case-study fade-in">
          <div class="case-meta">
            <span class="case-industry">Roofing</span>
            <span class="case-type">Lead Follow-Up Automation</span>
          </div>
          <div class="case-inner">
            <div class="case-text">
              <h2 class="case-title">Roofing Company Closes 31% More Estimates With Automated Follow-Up</h2>
              <div class="case-section">
                <h3 class="case-section-label">The Leak</h3>
                <p>A roofing company was generating consistent leads from door-to-door and digital ads — but only following up once or twice before moving on. When we audited, we found that 60% of their lost estimates went with a competitor — but when re-contacted 30+ days later, many said they "just hadn't gotten around to it yet." The leads weren't dead. The follow-up was.</p>
              </div>
              <div class="case-section">
                <h3 class="case-section-label">What We Implemented</h3>
                <p>An automated 8-touch follow-up sequence over 45 days — mixing SMS, email, and voicemail drops — each with different angles (urgency, social proof, seasonal timing). Leads that booked were automatically removed from the sequence. Leads that re-engaged were flagged for live follow-up by the sales team.</p>
              </div>
              <div class="case-section">
                <h3 class="case-section-label">The Result</h3>
                <p>In the first 90 days, the sequence re-engaged 22 leads previously marked as lost. 7 of them became closed jobs. Estimate close rate increased 31% overall. The system now runs automatically — every new lead enters the sequence the moment they're created in the CRM.</p>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="case-stats">
              <div class="case-stat case-stat--primary">
                <span class="case-stat-num">31%</span>
                <span class="case-stat-label">Increase in close rate</span>
              </div>
              <div class="case-stat">
                <span class="case-stat-num">7</span>
                <span class="case-stat-label">Closed jobs from "dead" leads</span>
              </div>
              <div class="case-stat">
                <span class="case-stat-num">90 days</span>
                <span class="case-stat-label">To first measurable results</span>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </article>

      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- WHAT TO EXPECT -->
    <section class="section-expect">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="expect-inner fade-in">
          <div class="section-label">Every Engagement</div>
          <h2 class="section-headline">What You Can Expect From Day One</h2>
          <div class="expect-timeline">
            <div class="timeline-item">
              <div class="timeline-day">Day 0</div>
              <div class="timeline-event">Free Leak Report audit — we map your operation and identify priorities</div>
            </div>
            <div class="timeline-item">
              <div class="timeline-day">Day 1–2</div>
              <div class="timeline-event">You receive your personalized Leak Report with specific opportunities and ROI estimates</div>
            </div>
            <div class="timeline-item">
              <div class="timeline-day">Day 3–4</div>
              <div class="timeline-event">We align on the first solution, configure it, and test it before showing you</div>
            </div>
            <div class="timeline-item">
              <div class="timeline-day">Day 5</div>
              <div class="timeline-event">You review and approve. We go live. Your first automation is working.</div>
            </div>
            <div class="timeline-item">
              <div class="timeline-day">Month 1+</div>
              <div class="timeline-event">We monitor, maintain, and identify the next leak to fix</div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- CTA -->
    <section class="section-cta">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="cta-inner fade-in">
          <div class="section-label">Your Business Could Be Next</div>
          <h2 class="cta-headline">Find Out What You're Leaking</h2>
          <p class="cta-sub">
            The audit is free. The Leak Report is yours to keep. And if we find something worth fixing —
            most clients are live within 72 hours.
          </p>
          <a href="/assessment" class="btn btn--white btn--lg">Get Your Free Leak Report →</a>
          <p class="cta-fine">No commitment. No sales pitch. Just your personalized opportunity report.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

  </main>

  <SiteFooter />
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  /* PAGE HERO */
  .page-hero {
    padding: 80px 0 72px;
    background: var(--color-bg);
  }

  .page-headline {
    font-size: clamp(36px, 5.5vw, 58px);
    font-weight: 700;
    line-height: 1.1;
    letter-spacing: -0.03em;
    color: var(--color-text);
    margin-bottom: 24px;
    text-wrap: balance;
  }

  .headline-accent {
    color: var(--pp-amber);
  }

  .page-sub {
    font-size: 18px;
    color: var(--color-body);
    line-height: 1.65;
    max-width: 540px;
  }

  /* RESULTS BAR */
  .results-bar {
    background: var(--color-bg-dark);
    padding: 36px 0;
  }

  .results-bar-inner {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 40px;
  }

  .results-stat {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    align-items: flex-start;
    gap: 5px;
  }

  .results-stat--hero .stat-num {
    font-size: 48px;
  }

  .stat-num {
    font-size: 32px;
    font-weight: 700;
    letter-spacing: -0.02em;
    color: #ffffff;
    line-height: 1;
    font-variant-numeric: tabular-nums;
  }

  .stat-num--md {
    font-size: 22px;
  }

  .stat-label {
    font-size: 12px;
    color: rgba(255,255,255,0.75);
    text-align: left;
  }

  .results-divider {
    width: 1px;
    height: 52px;
    background: rgba(255,255,255,0.15);
    flex-shrink: 0;
  }

  .results-pair {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 10px;
  }

  .results-pair-stat {
    display: flex;
    align-items: baseline;
    gap: 10px;
  }

  .results-pair-sep {
    height: 1px;
    background: rgba(255,255,255,0.1);
  }

  .results-note {
    max-width: 200px;
  }

  .results-note p {
    font-size: 14px;
    color: rgba(255,255,255,0.75);
    line-height: 1.5;
    margin-bottom: 10px;
  }

  .results-note strong {
    color: #ffffff;
  }

  .results-note-link {
    font-size: 13px;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--pp-sky);
    text-decoration: none;
    transition: color 0.15s;
  }

  .results-note-link:hover {
    color: #ffffff;
  }

  /* CASE STUDIES */
  .section-cases {
    padding: 96px 0;
    background: var(--color-bg);
  }

  .case-study {
    margin-bottom: 56px;
    padding-bottom: 56px;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border);
  }

  .case-study:last-child {
    border-bottom: none;
    margin-bottom: 0;
    padding-bottom: 0;
  }

  .case-meta {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 12px;
    margin-bottom: 20px;
  }

  .case-industry {
    font-size: 11px;
    font-weight: 700;
    letter-spacing: 0.08em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: #ffffff;
    background: var(--pp-navy);
    padding: 4px 10px;
    border-radius: var(--radius-pill);
  }

  [data-theme="dark"] .case-industry {
    background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.1);
    color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.9);
  }

  .case-type {
    font-size: 13px;
    color: var(--color-muted);
  }

  .case-inner {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 280px;
    gap: 48px;
    align-items: start;
  }

  .case-title {
    font-size: 24px;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--color-text);
    letter-spacing: -0.02em;
    margin-bottom: 28px;
    line-height: 1.25;
  }

  .case-section {
    margin-bottom: 24px;
  }

  .case-section-label {
    font-size: 11px;
    font-weight: 700;
    letter-spacing: 0.1em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--pp-amber);
    margin-bottom: 8px;
  }

  .case-section p {
    font-size: 15px;
    color: var(--color-body);
    line-height: 1.7;
  }

  .case-stats {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 24px;
    position: sticky;
    top: 80px;
  }

  .case-stat {
    background: var(--color-bg-section);
    border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    border-radius: var(--radius-md);
    padding: 20px;
    text-align: center;
  }

  .case-stat--primary {
    background: var(--pp-navy);
    border-color: transparent;
  }

  [data-theme="dark"] .case-stat--primary {
    background: oklch(18% 0.06 265);
    border-color: rgba(64, 165, 221, 0.2);
  }

  .case-stat-num {
    display: block;
    font-size: 40px;
    font-weight: 700;
    letter-spacing: -0.03em;
    color: var(--pp-amber);
    line-height: 1;
    margin-bottom: 6px;
    font-variant-numeric: tabular-nums;
  }

  .case-stat--primary .case-stat-num {
    font-size: 48px;
    color: var(--pp-sky);
  }

  .case-stat-label {
    font-size: 12px;
    color: var(--color-muted);
    line-height: 1.4;
  }

  .case-stat--primary .case-stat-label {
    color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.8);
  }

  /* EXPECT */
  .section-expect {
    padding: 80px 0 96px;
    background: var(--color-bg-section);
  }

  .expect-inner {
    max-width: 680px;
  }

  .expect-timeline {
    margin-top: 40px;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0;
  }

  .timeline-item {
    display: flex;
    gap: 24px;
    padding: 20px 0;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    align-items: flex-start;
  }

  .timeline-item:first-child {
    border-top: 1px solid var(--color-border);
  }

  .timeline-day {
    font-size: 13px;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--pp-amber);
    min-width: 80px;
    flex-shrink: 0;
    padding-top: 2px;
  }

  .timeline-event {
    font-size: 15px;
    color: var(--color-body);
    line-height: 1.55;
  }

  /* CTA */
  .section-cta {
    padding: 96px 0;
    background: var(--pp-navy);
  }

  [data-theme="dark"] .section-cta {
    background: var(--color-bg-dark);
  }

  .section-cta .section-label {
    color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.85);
  }

  .cta-inner {
    text-align: center;
    max-width: 620px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  .cta-headline {
    font-size: clamp(30px, 4.5vw, 48px);
    font-weight: 700;
    line-height: 1.1;
    letter-spacing: -0.03em;
    color: #ffffff;
    margin-bottom: 20px;
  }

  .cta-sub {
    font-size: 17px;
    color: rgba(255,255,255,0.88);
    line-height: 1.65;
    margin-bottom: 36px;
  }

  .cta-fine {
    margin-top: 16px;
    font-size: 13px;
    color: rgba(255,255,255,0.75);
  }

  /* RESPONSIVE */
  @media (max-width: 840px) {
    .case-inner {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }
    .case-stats {
      flex-direction: row;
      position: static;
    }
    .case-stat {
      flex: 1;
    }
    .results-divider {
      display: none;
    }
    .results-bar-inner {
      justify-content: center;
      gap: 32px;
      flex-wrap: wrap;
    }
    .results-pair {
      flex-direction: row;
      gap: 24px;
      align-items: center;
    }
    .results-pair-sep {
      display: none;
    }
    .results-note {
      text-align: center;
      max-width: none;
    }
  }

  @media (max-width: 480px) {
    .case-stats {
      flex-direction: column;
    }
  }
</style>
